-area by bazza\n\ntailwind classes to fix interaction dead zones. uses pseudo-elements to expand hit areas without messing up your layout.\n\nfinally a practical way to ship this across a whole codebase.\n\nhttps://bazza.dev/craft/2026/hit-area\nnpx shadcn@latest add https://bazza.dev/r/hit-area", "photos": ["https://cdn4.telesco.pe/file/PfhpkbYeDA79mN9aJifkBAbCyeXmV2Wpamvfq7DR3nBp8TTJ58ezfC5uHYCsqecH1L9tRATpJn94wVEoMrqjY07l0KuQq47xFfZR2-lsH1jVwIaAxU-dnrXIgPeRgBwj1rNCQLDmi19HBZebFYoMT7W2OfogNfPjF8jXBjy8shLmP9jEVvFs_vM0GjivDT1lqmZT6YkzSgso6F2bQRD9Qqc-RSYm4Ki_XeQmf7sd-e83MumiAXjmsEg2PF10YCrt-p7bxemKIkmuSHFFjvfRNwmL8VdqkI-p69wMQXBWq0MHv-Gw8uRj57CtXBw9liJAX3n3fA5a6GGtTYWZRIsS9w"], "videos": ["videos/24.mp4"]}, {"id": "23", "text": "cobe by shuding\n\nstunning 5kb webgl globe library for landing pages. ultra-light, customizable, and smooth as hell.\n\nhttps://cobe.vercel.app/\nnpm i cobe", "photos": ["https://cdn4.telesco.pe/file/N2DiKGkmpd2C0UVSssMzpyQxSkqp51rlRxCMqywwxFq3erNEpRhaX73QwSEKZS3eZIJBmC9F6Wnq-AZj89-4zVb2Od_UAXy9ngm2ZtUhoDsLy7EGMIDKWtbVd1TvS6r3Fow8tJHOvZWirUVarIH8Gni_LPEHnE-Y2ZnznzaBlTUCb0UnNZk6SukWZNzNZOhRutb68snLtRtOs1mXqsU0yfV3gUF2d94DQ-UgpNJbT0JyMp33XJNZZg_KoDCPiRYP0PVGe68A6oKtIEu3PwSWxxwK4UaWvTXgB-uDMIJdSElvw1wlNiDZMOZDAvEhe9nLKY--sYKjCWG_-WwAab9vfQ"], "videos": ["videos/23.mp4"]}, {"id": "22", "text": "someone just open sourced a full 3d building editor that runs in the browser. no autocad, no revit, no $5k licenses.\n\nit’s called pascal editor. built with react three fiber + webgpu for near-native speed.\n\nfeatures:\n- real-time building/wall hierarchy\n- gpu-powered ecs architecture\n- zustand state (undo/redo)\n- next.js frontend\n- dirty node tracking for fast renders\n\nyou can stack, explode, or solo levels and edit everything in 3d. firms pay $50k+ for bim software that does this.\n\nthis is 100% open source and free.\n\nhttps://editor.pascal.app/\nhttps://github.com/pascalorg/editor", "photos": ["https://cdn4.telesco.pe/file/UUZW80IoU50tAFChRm